.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-service-catalog-add - Register an additional community catalog source


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel service catalog add  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Register an additional catalog source -- a git repository laid out like the
official catalog (a top-level registry.yaml and services// subdirectories).
After adding a source, run 'citadel service catalog update' to fetch it.

.PP
The source name defaults to the repository name; override it with --name. The
built-in official source is always present and is named "default".


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for add

.PP
\fB--name\fP=""
	Name for the source (defaults to the repository name)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-service-catalog(1)\fP
